==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quickwork
<hw>Quick"work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> A
term somewhat loosely used to denote: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>All the
submerged section of a vessel's planking.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
planking between the spirketing and the clamps.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>The short planks between the portholes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quid</ent>⟦br⟧
